descript.abstract: This data layer represents Land use for Dane County, Wisconsin in 2000. [Parcel based land use inventory for Dane County for the year 2000.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [This data set was developed for site specific and regional planning including land use, transportation and environmental resource applications.]

stdorder.fees: A fee of $100 per civil township, for license to use and standard package of commonly requested data. Prices are subject to change without notice.
stdorder.ordering: Data can be order online using the Dane County GIS Data Order Form, http://www.co.dane.wi.us/lio/Gis/townbundle.htm. Fill out the online License Agreement for Dane County Digital Geographic Data Sets http://www.co.dane.wi.us/lio/Gis/licenseaggreement.pdf, providing licensing information and custom data requested. Mail or fax in the license agreement. A signed license agreement must be received before data can be released. All requests will be invoiced following delivery of the data.

distinfo.custom: An additional cost of $30/hour for staff time plus computer time and media charges is assessed for non-standard datasets or non-standard data file formats.
